Anthem Blue Cross has said the child's doctor is at fault for not submitting the required documents ahead of the legal deadline.

'Our records reflect that claim was denied because their doctor, despite efforts by Anthem to obtain this information, did not provide necessary documentation before the legal deadline to process a claim expired,' Darrel Ng, spokesman for Anthem Blue Cross told Fox News. 

The insurance company also said the family can appeal the decision that the chair is not necessary for Crue, according to ABC.

The toddler's parents plan to appeal the decision and keep fighting for their son.

