Aubrey began sharing her son's story on Facebook, which led a close friend of theirs to start a donation page to help raise funds so that Crue could have a new wheelchair.

As their friend, Chanda Clark Steggell, was only intending to raise $10,000, by Saturday $15,995 had been raised in donations.

Now Crue will also be able to have a standing walker and standing wheelchair.

The donations will also help with many other of his other medical needs that are incurred on both a weekly and monthly basis.

